The paper deals with the design and analysis of algorithms for a graph problem, specifically the problem of deciding whether an edge belongs to a sparse spanning graph of a given connected graph. This problem is related to graph theory, algorithms, and data structures, which are all covered by the arXiv sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.IT (Information Theory). Among these, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on the design and analysis of algorithms for a graph problem, which is a core topic in these sub-fields.
